        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:26PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Elton, or over Sandstone.

HAZARD...Rapid rises can be expected on creeks and streams.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Water issues are possible for low water crossings and in
low lying areas.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central
Raleigh County.
</description>
        <instruction>Do not drive your vehicle into areas where the water covers the
roadway. The water depth may be too great to allow your car to cross
safely.</instruction>
